subject: Football
lead_paragraph: Jordan Culbreath ran for 145 yards and 2 touchdowns last night as host Princeton held on for a 34-31 victory against Cornell.The teams traded scores for most of the night before the Tigers (3-4, 2-2 Ivy League) went ahead for good on Culbreath’s 58-yard touchdown run midway through the fourth quarter. Cornell (4-3, 2-2) had a chance to tie it with five seconds left, but a 48-yard field-goal attempt by Peter Zell sailed wide right.
